{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Welcome to Africa! Or rather, I should say, welcome home."},{"time":5000,"text":"Because this is where it all really began, isn't it?"},{"time":8000,"text":"Looking at fossils dating back several millions of years --"},{"time":11000,"text":"it all points to evidence that life"},{"time":13000,"text":"for the human species as we know it began right here."},{"time":19000,"text":"We are on an amazing journey the next four days."},{"time":23000,"text":"You're going to hear stories of \"Africa: The Next Chapter.\""},{"time":27000,"text":"Fantastic tales, anecdotes from speakers."},{"time":29000,"text":"But I want to turn that upside down for a moment,"},{"time":33000,"text":"and get something out on the table and clear the air so to say."},{"time":38000,"text":"What's the worst thing you've ever heard about Africa?"},{"time":41000,"text":"And this is not a rhetorical question."},{"time":42000,"text":"I actually want answers from you."},{"time":45000,"text":"Go for it! The worst."},{"time":48000,"text":"Famine."},{"time":50000,"text":"Corruption."},{"time":52000,"text":"More."},{"time":54000,"text":"Genocide."},{"time":56000,"text":"AIDS."},{"time":59000,"text":"Slavery."},{"time":63000,"text":"That's enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65000,"text":"We've all heard these things."},{"time":67000,"text":"But this is about Africa, the story we have not heard."},{"time":71000,"text":"The stories that we want to know,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and the stories that do exist about positive tales."},{"time":77000,"text":"A part of my talk is going to be about investment opportunities"},{"time":81000,"text":"that exist on this continent,"},{"time":83000,"text":"to separate the rhetoric from the reality, the fact from the fiction."},{"time":87000,"text":"To go to the actual data and statistics that exist"},{"time":90000,"text":"about the actual things that are happening on the ground"},{"time":93000,"text":"that make Africa a realistic investment opportunity and option for you."},{"time":100000,"text":"So let's get going because Africa,"},{"time":101000,"text":"to some degree, is on a turnaround."},{"time":105000,"text":"A turnaround in terms of how it manages its image,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and how it takes control of its own destiny."},{"time":112000,"text":"And turnarounds are part and parcel"},{"time":114000,"text":"of what I have focused on for most of my professional career."},{"time":118000,"text":"And it all started almost a decade ago,"},{"time":121000,"text":"as a young consultant at McKinsey &amp; Company"},{"time":123000,"text":"at their first African office in Johannesburg."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126000,"text":"And there we worked with leading CEOs"},{"time":129000,"text":"on African issues, and African companies on turnarounds,"},{"time":132000,"text":"making the companies not just the best in Africa"},{"time":135000,"text":"but the best globally."},{"time":137000,"text":"But I really formalized this focus on turnarounds"},{"time":141000,"text":"when I was completing my MBA in the United States."},{"time":144000,"text":"It all began with a fantastic phone call."},{"time":146000,"text":"It was from Rosabeth Moss Kanter,"},{"time":149000,"text":"Harvard Business School guru and a professor of mine."},{"time":151000,"text":"And she said, \"I want to write a case, Euvin --"},{"time":154000,"text":"a case on a public-sector leader"},{"time":156000,"text":"that has lessons for the corporate world.\""},{"time":160000,"text":"And the leader that came to mind was Nelson Mandela."},{"time":164000,"text":"Because Nelson Mandela, as he took over power"},{"time":167000,"text":"as the first democratically-elected president of South Africa,"},{"time":170000,"text":"faced a situation of a country"},{"time":172000,"text":"that could have slid into the abyss of chaos."},{"time":175000,"text":"But he started the country on a path of a positive cycle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"Now the case, \"Nelson Mandela: Change Leader,\""},{"time":182000,"text":"became part of the research base for a chapter"},{"time":185000,"text":"in Rosabeth's new book called \"Confidence.\""},{"time":189000,"text":"And \"Confidence\" became a New York Times bestseller"},{"time":193000,"text":"and topped Business Week's hardcover bestseller list."},{"time":196000,"text":"And why I tell you this story is because later, when I was interviewed"},{"time":199000,"text":"on SABC Africa, on a pan-African broadcast, they asked,"},{"time":202000,"text":"\"What is your key lesson, or the key thing you enjoy the most?\" --"},{"time":206000,"text":"because it was a huge privilege to be part of such a project."},{"time":209000,"text":"The lesson from that was that it was Africa -- an African story --"},{"time":214000,"text":"that was used to share news with the rest of the world"},{"time":218000,"text":"of what the benchmark can be for corporate turnarounds."},{"time":221000,"text":"Africa was being used as a success story!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"So I want to share with you a personal story"},{"time":228000,"text":"about a turnaround or a transformation."},{"time":230000,"text":"And that has to do with me"},{"time":232000,"text":"because in 1994, I packed a few things into a backpack"},{"time":236000,"text":"and headed off for a year of travel"},{"time":238000,"text":"in the middle of my university career."},{"time":241000,"text":"You should have seen my parents' reaction!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"But very soon, I found myself from the southern part of Africa,"},{"time":248000,"text":"in South Africa -- at the very north, in Egypt."},{"time":251000,"text":"And I sought out the most remote places."},{"time":253000,"text":"I went to the Siwa Oasis. That was one of my stops."},{"time":256000,"text":"And the Siwa Oasis is famous for several things,"},{"time":258000,"text":"but the key thing is that it was the place"},{"time":260000,"text":"that Alexander the Great went to"},{"time":263000,"text":"when he wanted to find out what his destiny had in store for him."},{"time":266000,"text":"And legend has it that Alexander trekked through this desert."},{"time":269000,"text":"Half his battalion was wiped out in the sandstorm."},{"time":272000,"text":"And myth says that he had an audience with the oracle,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and it foretold his destiny of greatness."},{"time":278000,"text":"This was 300 BC."},{"time":280000,"text":"So Africa had long been seen as a place to go to for answers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"Now, the thing I remember about Siwa"},{"time":289000,"text":"was the magical view of the sky at night."},{"time":292000,"text":"With no natural light source, Siva is one of these amazing places"},{"time":295000,"text":"that when you look up you see a perfect tapestry."},{"time":299000,"text":"Fast forward to 2002."},{"time":301000,"text":"I'm sitting in Cambridge, Massachusetts"},{"time":303000,"text":"at the Healthcare Development Conference."},{"time":305000,"text":"And I see the same picture, but from the opposite side."},{"time":308000,"text":"A satellite picture looking down at the earth."},{"time":313000,"text":"And it was that picture that made such a profound impact on me"},{"time":316000,"text":"because I'll never forget it. I remember the very moment."},{"time":319000,"text":"And I wanted to share that image with you of what I saw at that point."},{"time":325000,"text":"The first thing that I saw was North America at night --"},{"time":330000,"text":"glowing, in all its glory. A warm feeling. Light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340000,"text":"And then I saw it -- Africa. Quite literally the \"Dark Continent.\""},{"time":350000,"text":"And while Africa may be dark,"},{"time":352000,"text":"the thing that brought the message home to me"},{"time":355000,"text":"was that this is the challenge we are facing,"},{"time":358000,"text":"but it's also the opportunity."},{"time":361000,"text":"Because whilst Africa may be dark -- other than the few specks"},{"time":364000,"text":"that exist north and in the south and other areas --"},{"time":368000,"text":"it's aglow with the light in the hearts"},{"time":370000,"text":"of the millions of people that are there."},{"time":372000,"text":"Entrepreneurs, dynamic people, people with hope."},{"time":376000,"text":"It was George Kimble, the geographer, who said"},{"time":379000,"text":"that, \"The only thing dark about Africa is our ignorance of it.\""},{"time":384000,"text":"So let's start shedding light on this amazing eclectic continent"},{"time":388000,"text":"that has so much to offer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"Let's start unpacking it."},{"time":395000,"text":"Africa is the second-largest continent, a landmass second from Asia."},{"time":402000,"text":"It also is the second most populated continent,"},{"time":404000,"text":"with 900 million people."},{"time":406000,"text":"In fact -- coming back to the land mass -- Africa is so big"},{"time":409000,"text":"that you could fit in the continental United States,"},{"time":412000,"text":"China, and the entire Europe into Africa, and still have space."},{"time":417000,"text":"Africa is home to over 1,000 languages --"},{"time":420000,"text":"2,000 is another estimate that's out there --"},{"time":423000,"text":"with over 2,000 languages and dialects."},{"time":426000,"text":"But you could say, \"Invest in Africa in over 1,000 languages,"},{"time":430000,"text":"and it wouldn't make a difference.\""},{"time":433000,"text":"What does the data say?"},{"time":435000,"text":"As an investment banker, I'm in the cross-flow of information"},{"time":439000,"text":"and the changes that are taking place in capital markets."},{"time":442000,"text":"So I want to share with you some of these bellwether signals, or signs,"},{"time":445000,"text":"and winds of change that are sweeping this continent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"So let's start on that."},{"time":449000,"text":"And let's start at the high level, on the macro-factors."},{"time":451000,"text":"Inflation, in general, is coming down across Africa --"},{"time":454000,"text":"that's the first sign --"},{"time":456000,"text":"in many countries reaching double-digit figures."},{"time":458000,"text":"So let's start looking at some of those."},{"time":460000,"text":"I call it my Z.E.N. cluster."},{"time":462000,"text":"Zambia: from 2004 to 2006, moves from the 18 percent in inflation"},{"time":467000,"text":"to the nine percent."},{"time":469000,"text":"Egypt: from the 16 percent to about 8.4 percent."},{"time":474000,"text":"Nigeria: a similar situation,"},{"time":476000,"text":"from the 16 percent to the eight percent. Single digits."},{"time":482000,"text":"More fascinating, you have other countries -- South Africa,"},{"time":486000,"text":"Mauritius, Namibia -- all in single digits."},{"time":493000,"text":"But that's just part of the story. You have a similar trend with currencies --"},{"time":496000,"text":"currencies going through an extreme time of stability."},{"time":502000,"text":"But that's looking at the big picture."},{"time":504000,"text":"And the first myth to dispel is that Africa is not a country."},{"time":510000,"text":"It's made up --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513000,"text":"It's made up of 53 different countries."},{"time":517000,"text":"So the very definition -- to say \"invest in Africa\" is a no-go."},{"time":521000,"text":"It's meaningless."},{"time":523000,"text":"Each country has a unique value proposition."},{"time":526000,"text":"You can make money, you can lose money in Africa."},{"time":529000,"text":"But opportunities, boy oh boy, they exist."},{"time":532000,"text":"And this is what today is about --"},{"time":535000,"text":"it's about discussing those very opportunities."},{"time":539000,"text":"So let's start getting into the countries"},{"time":541000,"text":"and into the specific material and data."},{"time":546000,"text":"I was recently elected, as Emeka mentioned,"},{"time":548000,"text":"as the President of the South African Chamber of Commerce in America."},{"time":551000,"text":"And I'm very proud and happy to be in that role"},{"time":554000,"text":"because it is a fascinating position to be in."},{"time":556000,"text":"To hear this dialogue that's just increasing in tenor and velocity,"},{"time":560000,"text":"of decisions about trade and companies wanting to come."},{"time":564000,"text":"So the first port of call: let's talk a little bit about South Africa."},{"time":566000,"text":"But not the South Africa we always talk about --"},{"time":568000,"text":"the gold, the minerals, the First World infrastructure --"},{"time":571000,"text":"a bit about the other side of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573000,"text":"For example, South Africa was recently voted as the top destination"},{"time":577000,"text":"for the top 1,000 UK companies for offshore call-centers."},{"time":581000,"text":"Same language, timeline, et cetera. Makes sense."},{"time":586000,"text":"Other headlines that have recently reached South Africa"},{"time":588000,"text":"were Bain Capital and KKR, the big boys of private equity."},{"time":593000,"text":"Headline in South Africa: \"They have landed.\" Quite ominous."},{"time":596000,"text":"But what were they there for? To acquire assets."},{"time":600000,"text":"Bing Capital's acquisition of Edcon, a large retailer, is testimony"},{"time":607000,"text":"to the confidence they are starting to place in the economy."},{"time":610000,"text":"Because it is actually a long-term play."},{"time":612000,"text":"Being a retailer, it is a play on the belief"},{"time":614000,"text":"that this middle-class that's growing will continue to grow,"},{"time":618000,"text":"that the boom and the confidence in consumer spending will continue."},{"time":624000,"text":"But the story of Africa, and my focus, is beyond South Africa"},{"time":629000,"text":"because there's so much happening."},{"time":631000,"text":"Undoubtedly, Nigeria is clearly a hot spot."},{"time":635000,"text":"Challenges -- and we will hear a lot about Nigeria in these four days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"But looking at Goldman Sachs' work -- we had the famous BRIC Report."},{"time":644000,"text":"The new report, \"The Next Eleven,\" highlights that by 2020"},{"time":648000,"text":"Nigeria is going to be amongst the top 10 economies in the world."},{"time":652000,"text":"It's an investment opportunity. Think about that."},{"time":656000,"text":"Is anyone -- our banks, our investors --"},{"time":659000,"text":"seriously thinking about going to Nigeria?"},{"time":660000,"text":"If you haven't, why not?"},{"time":662000,"text":"What's going on in Nigeria? A couple of things."},{"time":666000,"text":"I want to talk about it from the perspective of capital markets."},{"time":670000,"text":"Bellwether signs again."},{"time":673000,"text":"Guarantee Trust Bank recently issued the first Euro Bond"},{"time":677000,"text":"out of Africa, and this excludes South Africa."},{"time":680000,"text":"But the first Eurobond, the raising of international capital"},{"time":683000,"text":"offshore, off its own balance sheet,"},{"time":686000,"text":"without any sovereign backing --"},{"time":688000,"text":"that is an indication of the confidence that is taking place in that economy."},{"time":692000,"text":"Without any sovereign backing,"},{"time":694000,"text":"a Nigerian company raising capital offshore."},{"time":696000,"text":"It's just a sign of things to come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"Looking at the oil industry, Africa provides 18 percent"},{"time":702000,"text":"of the U.S.'s oil supply, with the Middle East just 16 percent."},{"time":706000,"text":"It's an important strategic partner."},{"time":708000,"text":"Let's put Nigeria in perspective."},{"time":710000,"text":"2.2 to 2.4 million barrels of oil a day --"},{"time":713000,"text":"the same league as Kuwait, the same league as Venezuela."},{"time":718000,"text":"But with Africa, let's start being careful about this."},{"time":721000,"text":"And Emeka and I have had these discussions."},{"time":723000,"text":"We have to move away from what's called \"the curse of the commodities.\""},{"time":727000,"text":"Because it's not about oil, it's not about commodities."},{"time":729000,"text":"For Africa to truly be sustainable,"},{"time":731000,"text":"we have to move beyond to other industries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"So let's unpack those very quickly,"},{"time":736000,"text":"and I'm going to move through these very, very, very fast"},{"time":738000,"text":"because I can see that clock counting down."},{"time":742000,"text":"What else is going on there? Egypt."},{"time":745000,"text":"Egypt is launching a first large industrial zone --"},{"time":748000,"text":"2.8 billion investment."},{"time":750000,"text":"The announcement just came out the last few weeks."},{"time":752000,"text":"Close to the Mediterranean, near Alexandria --"},{"time":756000,"text":"textiles, petrochemicals."},{"time":758000,"text":"It's being managed by a Singaporean-based management company."},{"time":762000,"text":"So they want to emerge as an industrial powerhouse"},{"time":765000,"text":"across the industries -- away from oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"Let's look at agriculture. Let's look at forestry."},{"time":770000,"text":"What's going on there?"},{"time":771000,"text":"In Tanzania last week, we had the launch"},{"time":775000,"text":"of the East African Organic Produce Standard."},{"time":779000,"text":"Again, gathering together farmers, gathering together stakeholders"},{"time":784000,"text":"in East Africa to get standards for organic produce. Better prices."},{"time":791000,"text":"It ties in with small-scale farmers"},{"time":794000,"text":"in terms of no pesticides, no fertilizers."},{"time":799000,"text":"Again, opportunity to tackle markets to get that higher price."},{"time":804000,"text":"Uganda: the New Forest Company,"},{"time":806000,"text":"replanting and redeveloping their forests. Why is that important?"},{"time":812000,"text":"As the energy needs are met and electricity is needed [we will need]"},{"time":815000,"text":"poles for rolling out electricity."},{"time":817000,"text":"But here is the sweetener in the deal."},{"time":819000,"text":"They're going to be tapping into carbon credits."},{"time":823000,"text":"Let's go back to Nigeria."},{"time":825000,"text":"The banking sector has undergone tremendous transformation,"},{"time":828000,"text":"from over 80 banks to 25 banks. Strengthening of the system."},{"time":833000,"text":"But what's going on there? Only 10 percent of the country is banked."},{"time":838000,"text":"The largest population in Africa is in Nigeria."},{"time":841000,"text":"135 million-plus people. Think about that."},{"time":845000,"text":"There are only 700 ATMs in the country. Opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850000,"text":"The same for telecoms across the country."},{"time":853000,"text":"Now let's look at the continent as a whole."},{"time":855000,"text":"People look at the roads, for example, and they'd say,"},{"time":857000,"text":"\"Angola: 90 percent of roads are untarred. Ah, problem!\""},{"time":864000,"text":"It's more expensive to transport goods. Prices of goods go up,"},{"time":867000,"text":"inflation is affected."},{"time":869000,"text":"Nigeria: 70 percent of roads are untarred. Zambia: 80 percent."},{"time":872000,"text":"In general, more than 50 percent of roads are untarred."},{"time":875000,"text":"This is an opportunity! Energy needs -- it's an opportunity."},{"time":880000,"text":"So what are the signs that things are fundamentally changing?"},{"time":883000,"text":"Let's look at the stock markets in Africa."},{"time":886000,"text":"If I had to ask you, \"In 2005 what was the best performing stock market"},{"time":890000,"text":"or stock exchange in the world?\" Would Egypt come to mind?"},{"time":895000,"text":"In 2005, the Egyptian stock exchange returned over 145 percent."},{"time":903000,"text":"What's going on in some of the other countries?"},{"time":905000,"text":"Let's look at some 2006 numbers. Kenya: over 60 percent. Nigeria: over 40 percent."},{"time":912000,"text":"South Africa: in the 20 percents. High ones."},{"time":915000,"text":"These are the trends that are taking place."},{"time":921000,"text":"But in any investment decision, the key question is,"},{"time":925000,"text":"\"What is my alternative investment?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"Because in Africa today, we are competing globally for capital."},{"time":932000,"text":"And global capital is agnostic -- it has no loyalties."},{"time":937000,"text":"There's an overhang of capital in the U.S., and the key is yield pickup."},{"time":941000,"text":"What Africa is providing is a diversification play,"},{"time":944000,"text":"and also opportunities for yield pickup for the investor"},{"time":946000,"text":"that's aware of what he or she is doing."},{"time":950000,"text":"Now, when looking at Africa vis-a-vis other things,"},{"time":952000,"text":"and countries in Africa vis-a-vis other things,"},{"time":954000,"text":"comparisons become important."},{"time":956000,"text":"10 years ago there, were very few countries"},{"time":959000,"text":"that received sovereign ratings from"},{"time":960000,"text":"the Standard &amp; Poors, Moody's and Fitch's."},{"time":963000,"text":"Today, 16 African countries and growing"},{"time":967000,"text":"have sovereign country ratings. What does this mean?"},{"time":970000,"text":"Take Nigeria again: double B-minus --"},{"time":973000,"text":"in the league of Ukraine and Turkey. Immediately we have a comparison."},{"time":978000,"text":"The backbone of making investment decisions"},{"time":981000,"text":"for global holders of capital."},{"time":983000,"text":"Some other figures. South Africa: triple B-plus. Botswana: A-plus."},{"time":990000,"text":"Bakino Faso: B-minus. And so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":993000,"text":"In fact, one of the big agencies is setting up an office in Africa."},{"time":998000,"text":"Why are they doing that? Because they expect investment to follow."},{"time":1004000,"text":"So one of the big bellwethers,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and one of my final points I want to mention, is"},{"time":1009000,"text":"the interesting thing I read is that CNBC"},{"time":1011000,"text":"has launched their first African channel. Why is CNBC doing this?"},{"time":1016000,"text":"It's the 24-hour rolling African news channel."},{"time":1020000,"text":"They're doing it because they are expecting things to happen."},{"time":1023000,"text":"Me and you, the investments we are going to be making,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"the investments the world is going to be making --"},{"time":1028000,"text":"that's the 24-hour news channel dedicated to Africa."},{"time":1032000,"text":"So that's the change that's coming down the pipeline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1037000,"text":"So in conclusion, I want to turn back to that very slide"},{"time":1042000,"text":"that made such a deep impact on me all those years ago."},{"time":1047000,"text":"This time [I'll] give you the entire picture that I saw in 2002,"},{"time":1053000,"text":"and ask you that when you think about what your role can be in Africa,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"think about your journey in terms of bringing light to this continent."},{"time":1062000,"text":"Because there are amazing opportunities available."},{"time":1065000,"text":"And think about the concept of transformation"},{"time":1067000,"text":"in the back of your mind"},{"time":1069000,"text":"because things can be turned around rather quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073000,"text":"In 1899, Joseph Conrad released \"The Heart of Darkness,\""},{"time":1080000,"text":"a tale of grim horror along the Congo River."},{"time":1087000,"text":"If one looks carefully, on the Congo River"},{"time":1092000,"text":"is one of those bright lights. And that's the very Congo river"},{"time":1096000,"text":"generating light -- the old heart of darkness"},{"time":1099000,"text":"now generating light with hydro-electric power."},{"time":1102000,"text":"That is a transformation in power of ideas."},{"time":1105000,"text":"So the next step, over the next four days,"},{"time":1107000,"text":"is us exploring more of these ideas."},{"time":1110000,"text":"And perchance, if you can always keep this picture in your mind,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"that when we convene maybe in the distant future, in 2020,"},{"time":1118000,"text":"that picture will look very different."},{"time":1120000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1122000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}